{
  "texts": [
    "The ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, caused by the novel coronavirus SARS-CoV-2, has proven to be a significant global health crisis.",
    "First detected in Wuhan, China, in December 2019, the virus spread to nearly every part of the world, leading to unparalleled disruption.",
    "The rapid and widespread spread of COVID-19 has resulted in severe human and financial losses, and has had a significant impact on the healthcare system.",
    "There is an urgent need for early prediction of COVID-19 for effective future forecasting and efficient pandemic-tackling policy regulations, reducing strain on the medical care system [1] [2] [3] [4] [5] [6].",
    "Despite efforts to control the spread of the virus, an increase in the number of patients with viral mutations continues to be a major concern worldwide."
  ]
}